article.description: Corey Baldwin scored 22 points, matching his career best for the second time in four games, and five teammates also scored in double figures as North Dakota walloped Northern Arizona 101-59 on Th
article.headline: N. Dakota shoots lights out in 101-59 defeat of N. Colorado
article.linkText: N. Dakota shoots lights out in 101-59 defeat of N. Colorado
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Corey Baldwin scored 22 points, matching his career best for the second time in four games, and five teammates also scored in double figures as North Dakota walloped Northern Arizona 101-59 on Thursday night. Baldwin was 8 of 12 from the field with five 3-pointers, helping North Dakota(9-9, 4-3 Big Sky) to its highest score against a Division I team since joining D-I. North Dakota shot 61 percent from the field (39 of 64) with 14 3-pointers. Quinton Hooker scored 16 points for North Dakota, Cortez Seales 13, Adam McDermott 12, Drick Bernstine 11 and Conner Avants 10. Bernstine had a double-double with 11 rebounds, Hooker had eight assists with five steals, and Geno Crandall had six assists. Kris Yanku led the Lumberjacks (3-14, 1-5) with 17 points, eight rebounds and five assists, Alo Kaluna scored 12 points with a trio of 3-pointers and Felix Rivera-Vega added 11 points.
